  abstract-fetch layer per §7.1's two-stage strategy).
- 2C's `QueuePaperSummary.last_author` was typed `string | null` (right
  shape) but 2B's `screens/types.ts Paper.last_author` was typed
  `Author | null` (an object with first_name/last_name) — the two
  frontend-only type files disagreed with *each other*, not just with
  the backend.
- `QueueResponse` was missing the real `total_count` field (backend
  returns it; frontend only modeled `has_more`).
- `SavedItem` in the frontend assumed a `decided_at` field; the real
  backend `SavedItem` has no such field (it returns `position` instead,
  same as `QueueItem`).
- 2B's `Paper.publication_types: string[]` + a frontend-side
  `isRetracted()` string-matching helper predates 3A's later fix (see
  CONTRACTS.md's own change log, "Task 3A post-verification fix") that
