[2026-07-05T00:20:00] TASK 4B — PIVOT (real OAuth-callback contract mismatch, not hypothetical)
Confirmed by reading both sides' actual code (not just 2A's flagged
assumption): this was a genuine two-sided divergence, not one side
deviating from an agreed shape — CONTRACTS.md never pinned this
redirect at all, so both 2A and 3B independently guessed and guessed
differently.
- Frontend (`frontend/src/routes/ZoteroCallbackRoute.tsx`/
  `zoteroCallbackParams.ts`, Task 2A) expects the backend to redirect to
  its one real URL-based route (`/oauth/zotero/callback`) with
  `?status=success` or `?status=error&code=...&message=...`.
- Backend (`backend/app/routes/zotero.py`/`app/config.py`, Task 3B) on
  success redirected to `settings.zotero_post_auth_redirect_url`, whose
  *default* value was the SPA's home path (`/`) with an unrelated
  `?zotero=connected` param the frontend never parses — so a successful
  connect would never even land on `ZoteroCallbackRoute.tsx`, just the
  bare home screen with a param nobody reads. On failure
  (`ZoteroSessionMismatchError`/`ZoteroOAuthProviderError` in
  `auth_callback`, and `ZoteroOAuthProviderError` in `start_auth`), the
  backend returned a raw `{"error": {code, message}}` JSON body directly
  — but both of these routes are hit by a real browser navigation (the
  "Connect to Zotero" button does a full navigation to `/auth/start`;
  Zotero itself redirects the browser to `/auth/callback`), so a JSON
  body renders as an unstyled dead end, not an in-app error screen.
Resolution: backend was the side that needed to change — 2A's assumed
shape is the more SPEC-aligned one (§8.2 step 6 explicitly calls for
"bounces the browser to the fixed in-app post-auth path", and 2A had
already flagged its assumption in-code for exactly this confirmation).
Added `_callback_redirect()` in `backend/app/routes/zotero.py` (used by
all three failure paths across `start_auth`/`auth_callback`, plus
`auth_callback`'s success path) and changed
