First attempt at closing this gap was itself wrong, caught before
finishing: a draft test reached into `zoteroPushFlowStore` and called
`setPushPending(true)` directly before rendering `<App />`, then
asserted Disconnect required confirmation. This failed — not because
the guard was broken, but because the test's own premise was: `<App/>`
always mounts `<ZoteroPushModal />` unconditionally (it returns `null`
early only after its hooks run), so the *real*
`useZoteroPushFlowController` instance inside it is always live and its
own effect (`setPushPending(push.isPending)`) immediately overwrote my
manually-forced `true` back to `false` from its own (idle) mutation on
the very next effect pass — the same "handler-side counter runs in a
context you don't control" lesson as this task's earlier Playwright
`window` global mistake, just on the vitest/RTL side this time. Fixed by
driving a *genuinely* in-flight push through the real UI instead: open
the real push flow, pick a collection, click the real Save button
against a deliberately-held `POST /zotero/push` MSW response (same
`deferredPushHandler` technique as `useZoteroPushFlowController.test.tsx`),
then attempt Disconnect while that real mutation is still pending.

